description.plain:
Elena Jane “Ellie” Goulding (born 30 December 1986) – is an English singer-songwriter. In 2010, she became the second artist to both top the BBC’s annual Sound of… poll and win the Critics' Choice Award at the Brit Awards in the same year, following Adele’s win of both in 2008. Originally her music incorporated elements of folk, pop, electronica, and folktronica.

In July 2009, Goulding signed with Polydor Records, and released her debut EP An Introduction to Ellie Goulding, later that year. Her debut single, “Under The Sheets” was then released in November.

In 2010 Goulding recorded and released her debut record Lights, which spawned four charting singles in the UK, the biggest of which “Starry Eyes” peaked at #4 in the UK and charted in many European countries and Australia.

At the end of the year the album’s reissue Bright Lights was released, and spawned two singles: “Lights” and a cover of Elton John’s “Your Song.” The former of which propelled Goulding into international stardom after becoming a sleeper hit in the United States, eventually peaking at #2 after almost a year of the song charting.

In 2012, Goulding’s sophomore record Halcyon was released, featuring lead single ““Anything Could Happen”, which was another U.S. hit.

It’s re-issue, Halcyon Days saw critical acclaim for Goulding’s happier lyrical content and musical exploration into EDM. Its lead single, “Burn” was a top 20 hit in the United States, becoming a mega-success worldwide.

Goulding’s vocal connection with EDM has been explored through collaborations with Calvin Harris, on hits “I Need Your Love,” and “Outside”, as well as songs with Major Lazer, Clean Bandit, Zedd, Madeon, and Kygo.

The beginning of 2015 began with Goulding releasing her biggest hit to date, “Love Me Like You Do”“ for the 50 Shades of Grey Soundtrack. The song was acclaimed by critics and peaked at #1 around the world and #3 in the United States. The song garnered her a Best Pop Solo Performance Grammy Nomination.

Goulding later re-upped on her pop game with 2015’s Delirium. The album incorporated Goulding’s affiliation with club bangers and explored a poppier sound than her original albums. The album’s lead single “On My Mind” became an international success, and received media attention as speculated to be an answer song to Ed Sheeran’s “Don’t.” The album’s third single, “Something In The Way You Move” was another hit, peaking at #43 on the Hot 100.

2018 saw Goulding prepare for her fourth record. “Close To Me” with Diplo and featuring Swae Lee saw success, peaking at #24 in the U.S, and she followed these up with 2019’s “Flux” and “Sixteen” which are assumed to be album singles.

description.plain:
In this second single from the Fifty Shades of Grey film soundtrack, Ellie Goulding channels the character Anastasia Steele’s passion and desire.

Writing about this track in the Daily News, Jim Farber wrote:

With her little-girl-lost voice, Goulding sounds sweet even when she’s courting danger. The music, likewise, goes for a high gloss take on romance, recalling the heavily echoed beats and dense synthesizers of a Phil Collins ballad from the ‘80s.

The song spent four weeks at #1 on the UK singles chart and hit number three of the Billboard Top 100 in the US. Vaults made a remix that Ellie reposted on her SoundCloud. Later, it was included on her third album Delirium.

description.plain:
“On My Mind” is a song about the head going  places where the heart isn’t leading, a reversal of standard Pop lyric conventions.

The first single released in advance of Ellie Goulding’s 2015 album Delirium  became an international hit, charting in over 20 countries.

The song revolves around Ellie grappling with  lingering thoughts about an ex-lover and a lack of emotion about the relationship.

In an interview with Elvis Duran, Ellie explained how this unique viewpoint was created.

One day we were at the Max Martin compound, and we were just randomly talking about having somebody on your mind that shouldn’t necessarily be on your mind. And you can’t figure it out why they’re still there. I talked to friends about it, and I realized it was quite a common thing. Just having this strange situation of not necessarily being with that person anymore, but them still being around for whatever reason, and then just kind of trying to figure out why. So I think the song was the figuring out of why.

The song is seemingly about her relationship with singer Ed Sheeran, as a response to Sheeran’s previous single ‘Don’t’.

description.plain:
“Burn” is a song by English recording artist Ellie Goulding from Halcyon Days (2013), the reissue of her second studio album, Halcyon (2012). Originally a demo by Leona Lewis, “Burn” was released by Goulding in July 2013 as the lead single from the reissue.



Upon its release, “Burn” was met with a mixed response from music critics. They recognized that it may be the “radio-friendly” hit she needed, but questioned whether it would be the “pivotal track which will elevate her career even further in the mainstream radio world.”

It sold 116,857 copies in its first week and became Goulding’s first number-one single on the UK Singles Chart, where it would stay for three consecutive weeks.

The track achieved similar success internationally, reaching the top ten in Australia, Austria, Belgium, Germany, Ireland, Italy, New Zealand and Sweden. It was Goulding’s third single to reach the top twenty in the United States.

description.plain:
Ellie Goulding’s “Still Falling For You” is the lead single from the 2016 British romantic comedy Bridget Jones’s Baby, the third film in the film franchise and the sequel to 2004’s Bridget Jones: The Edge of Reason. The lyrics premiered on Genius on Aug. 18, 2016, and the song’s audio will be released globally on Aug. 19. She cryptically teased the song on Aug. 10 with a vague tweet:
https://twitter.com/elliegoulding/status/763479455574663170

description.plain:
On “Lights”, British singer-songwriter and producer Ellie Goulding talks about literally not being able to sleep with the light off. Over the synthpop production courtesy of Ashe Howes and Richard Stannard, “Lights” is intense yet calming all in one.

Despite only reaching #49 in the U.K. “Lights” performed extremely well around the world and propelled Goulding to a newfound musical success. After spending 33 weeks on the chart, “Lights” became a sleeper hit, peaking at #2 on the Billboard Hot 100, and spent over a year on the chart; a feat few songs have achieved. It reached the top 10 and 20 of numerous other countries.

“Lights” was released on February 16, 2011 as the second single from Bright Lights, the reissue of her debut album Lights.

It’s the third (or fourth, when you look at the premium version) single off of Ellie Goulding’s third album Delirium, it was released on October 29, 2015.

description.plain:
Described as the most positive song on the album by Goulding due to it’s uplifting nature, “Anything Could Happen” is the lead single and third track from Halcyon, the sophomore studio album by English singer and producer Ellie Goulding.

Released on August 17, 2012, the album charted at #5 in the UK, #20 in Australia and #47 in the United States. It also garnered positive reviews from critics who enjoyed Goulding’s vocals and the songs lyrics.

The song was produced by Jim Elliot & Ellie Goulding, who both wrote the track. They even invited the London Community Gospel Choir to assist Goulding on the track, you can hear their work at the end of “Anything Could Happen”.

description.plain:
“How Long Will I Love You” is a song by English recording artist Ellie Goulding from Halcyon Days (2013), the reissue of her second studio album, Halcyon (2012). Released on November 10, 2013, as the second single from the reissue, “How Long Will I Love You” is a cover of the lead single from The Waterboys' fifth studio album, Room to Roam (1990).

“How Long Will I Love You” is also included on the soundtrack for the 2013 film About Time.

description.plain:
The promo single off Halcyon, Goulding’s new album. The song is a cover of the original Active Child song. Tinie Tempah pops in for a feature on alternate single which was originally (but not anymore) released as a free single on her soundcloud. They also collaborated on his song “Wonderman”

The original by Active Child
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WgJJc0H0enU
The tracklist on her album even states that the writers are Patrick James Grossi (Active Child) and Ariel Rechtshaid. Ellie’s name is nowhere to be found which means she has given credit where credit is due.

Active Child has stated that he is impressed with this cover and that it is

an incredibly proud moment for me as an artist."

description.plain:
Ellie has claimed that she has a huge fascination with classical music and opera singers and wanted to try it out on the track.

She spoke about the song with Michael Parkinson on Parkinson Masterclass in 2013; about how the song is about somebody who pushes people away their whole life without realising it, and as the world is coming to an end, all these explosions and they’ve got no one with them as the world ends – though she went on to say it could be interpreted in different ways.

description.plain:
A song about feeling completely depleted and weakened, “My Blood” serves as the second track from English singer and producer Ellie Goulding’s sophomore album Halcyon. Ellie has stated in the past it’s her favourite song to sing from Halcyon.

Produced, recorded and written by Goulding with producer Jim Elliot, the song takes on a ethereal yet darkened sound with a sonically-gradual build, untill everything drops off leaving hums to finish the track.

“My Blood” was released on October 5, 2012 alongside its parent album Halcyon, via Polydor Records.

description.plain:
Ellie Goulding explains her one-sided relationship on the dubstep-electro rock crossover “Figure 8.”

The song was the second single to be released from Halcyon, her second studio album. It also appears on Halcyon Days, it’s repackage.

The song see’s Ellie attempting to hold onto the relationship, similarly to previous album track “Halcyon.” It was produced by Jonny Lattimer, I SEE MONSTAS & Mike Spencer, and released on October 5, 2012 alongside it’s parent album.

description.plain:
“Goodness Gracious” is about someone who keeps going back to their ex because they are desperately in love even though the on/off-relationship is toxic and doomed to fail.

Goulding explained the meaning behind this song to Rolling Stone, saying;

I’ve been in situations where I knew someone wasn’t right for me, yet I kept bringing them back. […] [the song] is about dissing yourself for not thinking straight and not being fair.

The single peaked at #16 in the UK, #5 in Belgium, the top 30 in a few European countries and the top 40 in Australia.

description.plain:
“Don’t Need Nobody” is a powerful pop song about Ellie’s strong attachment to someone. Featuring production by the legendary pop producer Max Martin and The Struts, the song builds to a climax in the chorus when the beat finally gives way and the song becomes danceable in a whole new way.

It’s the tenth song from Ellie Goulding’s third album Delirium, which was released on 6 November 2015.

description.plain:
Ellie’s ode to her father details their relationship when she was younger. She spoke about the song with Michael Parkinson on Parkinson Masterclass in 2013, talking about how the song came about; how she didn’t think her father cared, but how she is now more sympathetic about the situation:

If I spent the rest of my life being bitter about it, I’d never get on with anything.

description.plain:
Tessellation is an art of mathematics that focuses on shapes to form polygons which in turn make a beautiful design. Like the work of M.C. Escher or a mosaic.



Tessella in Greek means “small triangle.” The story of the song has the biggest focus on this line

“Triangles are my favorite shape
Three points where two lines meet

Alt-J has stated:
ON ∆S AND BAND NAMES: We’re not particularly obsessed with the shape. There’s our song “Tessellate” where there is a line, “Triangles are my favorite shape"—it was a suitable line to say in the context of the song. The song was about tessellations and triangles fit really well together. We only really chose Alt-J because it was a name we could all agree on. We had to change our name because we were originally called FILMS but there is an American band named The Films. We spent a month and half trying to figure out what this new name should be and we were really getting desperate to decide, and we didn’t have to compromise on this one, we all liked it.

Well we already know, the elegant and beautiful Ellie likes to cover songs that she likes. For a second time she teams up with Chiddy’s producer “The Almighty” Xaphoon Jones to cover Alt-J’s song Tessellate

The song could also be a reference to the band themselves considering their name is Alt-J which is an allusion to the Greek Delta (press on alt+J if you have a mac)



Xaph even adds a little twist of Jazz to structure the song in a different type of eloquence. That sexy sax sounds so sensual. Vibe out.

The song is more designed like a poem with a repetition of certain stanzas for emphasis on the structure which resembles a tessellation.

It’s very similar to a movie like Catch 44., which focuses on three people. Like a weird violent and deceitful love triangle.

description.plain:
“I Do What I Love” is a song from the deluxe version of Ellie Goulding’s third album Delirium, which was released on 6 November 2015.

Featuring experimental, percussion-driven production with middle eastern influences (similarly to “Aftertaste”), Ellie simply tells it how it is; she’s stronger than ever as a person, and she’s doing what she loves.

description.plain:
Hollow Crown is Ellie Goulding’s contribution to the Game of Thrones inspired compilation album For The Throne.

Sam Harris, co-writer of the song, confirmed to Making Game of Thrones that Hollow Crown takes the perspective of Jaime Lannister as he addresses his twin sister and former lover Cersei, the queen of Westeros.

That is fully a Cersei and Jaime song, it’s this idea of how Jaime felt he was going to be there with Cersei no matter what, but she pushed him away because she’s so power hungry… fighting a losing battle.

https://vignette.wikia.nocookie.net/gameofthrones/images/d/dc/Jaime_%26_Cersei_S8_Ep5.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/2000?cb=20190513025906

Two days before release, Goulding posted a snippet of the song on her Twitter.
https://twitter.com/elliegoulding/status/1121093069074513926

description.plain:
“Devotion” is a song of Ellie Goulding’s third album Delirium, which was released on November 6th, 2015. It serves as the penultimate track on the standard edition of the album.

Lyrically the song talks about being completely devoted to a person, but for Ellie it’s about her devotion to music.

The song was written by Ellie Goulding, Stephen Wrabel and it’s producers; Ali Paymi and Klas Ahulnd.

Lyrically the song talks about being completely devoted to a person, but for Ellie it’s about her devotion to music.

The song was written by Ellie Goulding, Stephen Wrabel and it’s producers; Ali Paymi and Klas Ahulnd.

description.plain:
In an interview with Digital Spy, when asked about the meaning of the song (and the claim that it is happier than some of her previous work), Goulding replied:

It’s about letting go. As opposed to all the sad and depressing things I write about, I decided to write something about the joining together of people in some kind of euphoric state – be it at a festival, at a show or in a club. I wanted a song that would reach out to people of every background and every enjoyment, whether you enjoy a natural high, taking drugs, drinking or whatever. Because I’m essentially a pop artist I wanted to write a song that everyone can relate to.

description.plain:
On “Only You”, Ellie Goulding reflects on her lover being an enemy and an ally. It serves as the fourth track for Ellie’s second album Halcyon.

The song was referred to as “somewhere in between, thunderous and electrifying but bereft of the kind of earworms that would make it compulsively replayable”.

Structurally different from many of Goulding’s works in the past, “Only You” is comprised of only Chorus'.

description.plain: Ellie Goulding stated that “Holding On For Life' is a bit more of a philosophical one for me. It’s more about being with someone, and it being kind of now or never, and it’s a matter of life or death. And you feel like there’s still a lot of life left in you and the other person, but you’re just trying to hold on to it, and hold on to what you’ve got.”

description.plain:
Ellie Goulding attempts to shine the line on a damaged relationship on “Halcyon”, the title track to her second album.

The meaning of the song lies in the title “Halcyon” which according to Wikipedia is a species of birds that held the “ancient belief that the bird nested on the sea, which they calmed in order to lay its eggs on a floating nest. Two weeks of calm weather were therefore expected around the winter solstice. This myth leads to the use of halcyon as a term for peace or calmness.”

Ellie Goulding is comparing herself to the Halcyon bird, calming the “sea” (or the turmoil in her relationship) for a short period of peace during the “winter” (the dark period/end of their relationship). Nautical references are a big theme on this album which links it back to the its title Halcyon.

description.plain:
“Two Years Ago” is a song from the Target edition of Ellie Goulding’s third album Delirium, which will be released on 6 November 2015.

During an interview with Refinery29, Goulding revealed the name of a new track called “Two Years”.

I have a song on the album that is called ‘Two Years’. It’s about two years ago, which is before I met my boyfriend. I’m really curious about him. He’s my boyfriend, so I’ll write about him and his past and the things he’s been through. It’s pretty amazing stuff and he’s a pretty incredible person.

description.plain:
On “Joy” (stylised in capitals on Spotify & Soundcloud), Ellie Goulding learns that her lover no longer brings her happiness.

Featuring a whirlwind pickup towards the end, Ellie turns sadness into a moment of pure clarity with her ethereal vocals swelling over a string section and live backing drums.

The heavily orchestrated track features production from Goudling and frequent collaborator Jim Elliot who produced 6 other tracks from parent album Halcyon with her. “Joy” is also featured on the extended repackage released a year later entitled Halcyon Days.

Ellie Goulding once said in an interview that a lot of her second album, Halcyon was about heartbreak. She said: “Sometimes I’d look at the lyrics I was coming up with and realise that I had all this sadness inside me.”

“Intro (Delirium)” is a song by English singer, songwriter and producer Ellie Goulding which appears as the introductory track on her third  studio album Delirium, which was released on 6 November 2015. It features operatic vocal chops over a dramaticly cinmeatic instrumental made in order to connect ellie’s previous ablum  Halcyon to Delirium.

The album itself (Halcyon) featured light, airy and often soprano vocals that help this connection to be deepened.

description.plain:
Something huge suddenly disappears – Ellie Goulding

The track is built on this concept. Ellie was inspired by her day-to-day talks with the producer, Jim Eliot. She mentioned that the chorus hones in on the emotional feeling of loss.

Produced with Eliot, Ellie sings about someone new and unique disappearing and the loss she felt afterwards. Over a mix of orchestrated pop and maximalist synthpop, Ellie’s voice soars in this interesting piece of pop called “Atlantis.”

The penultimate track to her second studio, Halcyon and later released on it’s reissue, Halcyon Days, “Atlantis” was released on October 5, 2012.

description.plain:
During an interview with SkySongs, Ellie commented on the meaning behind the song:

I wrote ‘Guns And Horses’ about a romance that began online, hence the lyric ‘you found me at a screen you sit at permanently.’ I wanted the guy to feel more than he did for me but through no fault of his own he couldn’t. It’s a song about frustration essentially. My producer [Starsmith] made me laugh at the end, I can’t repeat what he called me though.

The song was used in the sixth episode of the second season of the American television series Drop Dead Diva, “Begin Again,” originally aired 18 July 2010.

description.plain:
Ellie posted this cover of James Blake’s 2013 song to her SoundCloud page on the 2nd February 2014.

Ellie had previously shown a liking for the song on her Twitter, quoting one of its lyrics back in 2013:

https://twitter.com/elliegoulding/status/407590911758331904

Upon release, Spin magazine praised the track, noting that Angel Haze’s rap contribution was “fiercer and more personal” than that by Chance the Rapper in the song’s official remix.

Though never officially released, Ellie often performed the song live during her 2015 Halcyon Days tour.

description.plain:
‘Do You Remember’ is a song recorded by Ellie Goulding for the 2019 biographical sports comedy Fighting with My Family, directed by Stephen Merchant. The song is track 3 on the soundtrack, released on February 22.

In March 2018, Caspar Jopling (Goulding’s now-fiancé) teased the song with two snippets on his Instagram Story. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g_mTRjNDJNE

In February 16, 2019, Goulding announced the song in a teaser on Twitter along with a release date of February 22, coinciding with the release of the soundtrack.

https://twitter.com/elliegoulding/status/1096614820135219200

Star and executive producer Dwayne ‘The Rock’ Johnson, tweeted to Goulding, praising her and the song for “[her] talents and passion.”

https://twitter.com/TheRock/status/1096649929353773058

description.plain:
“Bittersweet” is the third song played in the end of credits of “Breaking Dawn: Part 2”, and is track 2 of “The Twilight Saga: Breaking Dawn – Part 2” Soundtrack.





The song was a collaboration between British singer Ellie Goulding and Goulding produced the song with her then-boyfriend, the American electronic artist and producer Skrillex. She told MTV News that though the tune turned out to be a perfect fit for the movie’s storyline, that wasn’t her intention upon writing it. “Myself and Skrillex got together in the studio and started working on this song, and it’s about waking up in the morning and hoping that the person feels the same way as you,” she said.

“For some reason, every single lyric just ended up relating to this film. And I think when it was played at some point to the Twilight people, they were like, ‘Oh my God!’ So they asked us if we were interested in being on the soundtrack and we were like, ‘Hell yeah!’”

description.plain:
Your Biggest Mistake is about Ellie’s father. He left his family when Ellie was 5. This song was written as message to her dad and all the question about leaving his family behind.

“I don’t really speak to him, and I think I got everything into that song that I could,” she told Spinner UK.

The lyrics and Ellie’s amazing voice conveys melancholy of a daughter who grew up without dad. There is a sense of betrayal felt by child brought up by single parents.

description.plain:
“Salt Skin” was the last song made for Ellie’s Album and the only one that really involves her finding love.

She originally had second thoughts about the track but changed her mind once it was mastered.

Many people believe that salt skin is actually about tears but it’s really about sweat in allusion to one of her favorite things to do, run. She even competes in marathons, but she’s running toward someone in particular.

description.plain:
A welcome break from the heavy electronica and intense electropop of the new additions to Halcyon, Ellie Goulding wishes for stillness on piano ballad “Hearts Without Chains.”

Produced by Adele collaborator Fraster T Smith, the song was originally released as the 17th track from Halcyon Days, the reissue of Ellie Goulding’s sophomore album.

Originally by Midnight Star, Ellie Goulding collaborates English DJ and producer BURNS to release Midas Touch. The track is featured on the re-issue of Goulding’s critically acclaimed album ‘Halcyon’ named ‘Halcyon Days released on August 26th.

Ellie Goulding can be seen dancing to the original Midas Touch in former producer Starsmith’s video from 2010.

description.plain:
“Wish I Stayed” is an electronic ballad about missing home: it was one of the first songs Ellie has ever written, when she was only eighteen years old.
The track evokes the memories of a young Ellie, when she had to quit her home in the countryside in order to move to London: she eventually regrets leaving Hertfordshire, as only once she moved away she really appreciated the place where she grew up.
Thus far, this is the only song in Ellie’s official discography that was written solely by her.

English singer-songwriter Ellie Goulding’s debut album, Lights both celebrates romance and anticipates the love hangover to come. She told to NME:

I spent the majority of my time recording this album in my producer Starsmith’s bedroom in Bromley. It is made up of songs that all started on a guitar over a period of about two years. A number of the songs vent romantic victories and failures."

description.plain:
Mixing intense indie-pop and enchanting electronica, Ellie Goulding can see her own personal progress after a breakup on “Without Your Love.”

Produced by frequent collaborators Starsmith who produced the majority of her debut Lights, “Without Your Love” was originally released as the 16th track from the international deluxe edition of Halcyon Days, the reissue of Goulding’s second studio album Halcyon.

songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
When did life become so complicated?
Years of too much thought and time I wasted
And in each line upon my face
Is proof I fought and lived another day
When did life become this place of madness?
Drifting on an empty sea of waves and sadness?
I make believe I'm in control
And dream it wasn't all my fault

[Chorus 1]
When your feet don't touch the ground
When your voice won't make a sound
Here, it's safe, in this place, up off the clouds
When your feet don't touch the earth
You can't feel the things that hurt
And you're free, there's no need to come down
When your feet don't touch the ground

[Verse 2]
Everyday just feels a little longer
Why am I the only one not getting stronger?
Running around pretending life's a play
It doesn't make the darkness go away
I may be young but I can still remember
Feeling full of joy, crying tears of laughter
Now all my tears are all cried out
Make believe, but count me out

[Chorus 2]
Cause my feet are on the ground
And the inner voice I found
Tells the truth and there's no use
If your head's in the clouds
With my feet on solid earth
I can face the things that hurt
And in time, I'll be fine
I'll come 'round

[Bridge]
I was once like you, life was a maze
I couldn't find my way out
But what I say is true, and you will be amazed
Make believe and you will find out that it's time

[Chorus 3]
When your feet don't touch the ground
When your voice won't make a sound
Here, it's safe in this place above the clouds
When your feet don't touch the earth
You can't feel the things that hurt
And you're free, there's no need to come down
When your feet don't touch the ground

description.plain:
“Father” is an original song written by Ellie Goulding about how being abandoned by her dad as a child.

In an interview, Ellie says that her dad leaving “left her emotionally ­damaged and unable to trust boyfriends.”
http://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/ellie-goulding-admits-being-abandoned-3222255

“I did find it hard to trust people when my dad left. Particularly men. I have gotten over that now but I thought if I had a boyfriend I would wonder why they were being so nice to me.”

“We used to see each other every other weekend and then once a month, and then never.
When I first stopped seeing him [her father] I can’t remember why and it has been too long now. I don’t know what he’s like now.”

Ellie put her heartbreak into words as a child by writing diaries which later translated into songs.

She said: “I used to be angry and bitter. I did not think he cared. But I became peaceful with it. If I spent the rest of my life being bitter I would never get on with anything. Song writing is a form of therapy, I think.”

body.plain:
“Father” is an original song written by Ellie Goulding about how being abandoned by her dad as a child.

In an interview, Ellie says that her dad leaving “left her emotionally ­damaged and unable to trust boyfriends.”
http://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/ellie-goulding-admits-being-abandoned-3222255

“I did find it hard to trust people when my dad left. Particularly men. I have gotten over that now but I thought if I had a boyfriend I would wonder why they were being so nice to me.”

“We used to see each other every other weekend and then once a month, and then never.
When I first stopped seeing him [her father] I can’t remember why and it has been too long now. I don’t know what he’s like now.”

Ellie put her heartbreak into words as a child by writing diaries which later translated into songs.

She said: “I used to be angry and bitter. I did not think he cared. But I became peaceful with it. If I spent the rest of my life being bitter I would never get on with anything. Song writing is a form of therapy, I think.”

description.plain:
In this song, Xaphoon Jones remixes Ellie Goulding’s 2010 hit song “Lights”. Xaphoon also used a sample of Goulding on the song “Wonderman”, which also appears on this mixtape.

Xaphoon Jones has an extensive history of working with Ellie Goulding and samples of her voice. Before this song was released, he sampled her in the Chiddy Bang song “Under The Sheets”. After the release of this song, Xaphoon produced the Ellie Goulding songs “High For This” and “Tesselate”. Ellie Goulding also provided backing vocals for the Chiddy Bang song “Out 2 Space”. He also creates a mashup using “High For This” on his third mixtape.

songs.lyrics:
Your name froze on the winter air
An empty bench in Soho Square
Forgotten now I turn away
Just save me for a rainy day
But don't be sorry, I don't want to hear it baby

My feet froze in the winter chill
I knew I'd probably get ill
But I was praying we could fill an empty bench and still
You're so sorry but I don't want your pity baby

It's all yours now please don't tease
The pigeons shiver in the naked trees
And I'll do anything but please don't hurt me
Just kiss me quick 'cos it's my birthday
And I feel so small I don't know why but no I'm not too old to cry

An empty bench in Soho Square
If you'd have come you'd have found me there
But you never did 'cos you don't care and I'm so sorry baby
I don't mind loneliness too much but when I met you I was touched
And that was good enough for me but do we always have to be sorry
Why can't we just be happy baby?

One day you'll be waiting there, no empty bench in Soho Square
And we'll dance around like we don't care
And I'll be much too old to cry
And you'll kiss me quick in case I die before my birthday

One day you'll be waiting there, no empty bench in Soho Square
No I don't know the reason why I'll love you till the day I die
But one day you'll be waiting there
Come summertime in Soho Square
And I'll be painting stars up in the sky
Before I get too old to cry before my birthday
I hope I see those pigeons fly before my birthday
In Soho Square on my birthday
